label: Created
definition: The date on which the resource was created.

label: References
definition: From EOL. It represents the references that an element could have, in one or more of the different format and schemas: BICI, CODEN,DOI, EISSN, HANDLE, ISBN, ISSN, LSID, OCLC, SICI, URL, URN
notes: eol:referenceType

label: Modified
definition: The Modified is the last date that the record was changed.
notes: From GISIN: SpeciesStatus. http://www.gisin.org/cwis438/websites/GISINDirectory/Tech/ProtocolSpecification.php#4.4.1.1

label: Start Valid Date
definition: The StartValidDate and EndValidDate represent the range of when a "status" data Model is valid. Data providers should return an empty element for the EndValidDate if the status is still current.
notes: From GISIN: SpeciesStatus. http://www.gisin.org/cwis438/websites/GISINDirectory/Tech/ProtocolSpecification.php#4.4.1.1

label: End Valid Date
definition: The StartValidDate and EndValidDate represent the range of when a "status" data Model is valid. Data providers should return an empty element for the EndValidDate if the status is still current.
notes: From GISIN: SpeciesStatus. http://www.gisin.org/cwis438/websites/GISINDirectory/Tech/ProtocolSpecification.php#4.4.1.1

label: Language
definition: Language used to write the species information, use ISO 639-2 vocabulary.

label: Citation
definition: Publication date of the current version.

label: Memo
definition: A GISIN term, part of its "SpeciesStaus" protocol , defined as  "An unsearchable field for providers to add anything else they think is important"

label: Publication Date
definition: Publication date of the current version.
notes: From GISIN: SpeciesStatus. http://www.gisin.org/cwis438/websites/GISINDirectory/Tech/ProtocolSpecification.php#4.4.1.1

label: Atomized Annual Cycle
definition: AnnualCycles element in structured format.

label: Unstructured Annual Cycle
definition: AnnualCyles element in text block format.

label: Start Time Interval
definition:
The date-time or interval at which an event starts. Recommended best practice is to use an encoding scheme, such as ISO 8601:2004(E).

A controlled vocabulary is recommended.
notes: e.g. "1963-03-08T14:07-0600" is 8 Mar 1963 2:07pm in the time zone six hours earlier than UTC, "2009-02-20T08:40Z" is 20 Feb 2009 8:40am UTC, "1809-02-12" is 12 Feb 1809, "1906-06" is Jun 1906, "1971" is just that year, "2007-03-01T13:00:00Z/2008-05-11T15:30:00Z" is the interval between 1 Mar 2007 1pm UTC and 11 May 2008 3:30pm UTC, "2007-11-13/15" is the interval between 13 Nov 2007 and 15 Nov 2007.

label: End Time Interval
definition:
The date-time or interval at which an event ends. Recommended best practice is to use an encoding scheme, such as ISO 8601:2004(E).

A controlled vocabulary is recommended.
notes: e.g. "1963-03-08T14:07-0600" is 8 Mar 1963 2:07pm in the time zone six hours earlier than UTC, "2009-02-20T08:40Z" is 20 Feb 2009 8:40am UTC, "1809-02-12" is 12 Feb 1809, "1906-06" is Jun 1906, "1971" is just that year, "2007-03-01T13:00:00Z/2008-05-11T15:30:00Z" is the interval between 1 Mar 2007 1pm UTC and 11 May 2008 3:30pm UTC, "2007-11-13/15" is the interval between 13 Nov 2007 and 15 Nov 2007.

label: Event
definition:
An action that occurs at some location during some time.

A controlled vocabulary is recommended.

label: Abstract
definition: A brief summary of the most relevant or attractive features of this tax√≥n to the general public.  Could point to any kind of information.
notes: Example: Blue whale is the largest mammal in the world.

label: Taxon Record id
definition: Unique identifier of the record within the database.

label: Atomized Common Names
definition: commonNames element in structured format.

label: Common Names
definition: The name of the common name.

label: Name
definition: The name of the common name.

label: Language
definition: Language used to write the species information, ISO 639-2 according to GBIF Metadata Profile.

label: Used In
definition: Location where de common name is used.

label: Used By
definition: Sometimes names used by one group of people are adopted by another.

label: unstructured common names
definition: CommonNames element in text block format.

label: Unstructured Demography And Threat
definition: demographyAndThreat element in unstructured format.

label: Legislation
definition: A national proposed law or group of laws. A regional proposed law or group of laws.

label: territory
definition: Information, mostly associated to vertebrates, referring to the territorial extension of the individual or group in terms of its activities (feeding, mating, etc.).

label: threat status
definition: Information about the conservation status of the taxon.

label: population biology
definition: Description of the variations in time and space, as well as in the size and density of populations, and the factors that cause such variations.

label: Atomized Dispersal
definition: Dispersal element in structured format.

label: Atomized Legislation
definition: legislation element in structured format.

label: Unstructured Legislation
definition: legislation element in text block format.

label: Legislation Type
definition: National and/or regional law or group of laws.

label: Legislation Name
definition: Word or phrase to designate the law or group of laws.

label: Protection Legal Status
definition: Description of the legal status.

label: Legislation Read
definition: The oficial document in which the user can read the legislation.

label: Status
definition: Whether a piece of legislation is in force, or superseded, etc.

label: Type
definition: Category of the piece of legislation.

label: Norm
definition: Norms are general legal principles that are widely accepted. This acceptance is evidenced in a number of ways, such as international agreements, national legislation, domestic and international judicial decisions, and scholarly writings.

label: Applies to
definition: Location where the status is used.

label: Unstructured Dispersal
definition: Dispersal element in text block format.

label: Purpose
definition: Makes reference to any data being measured.

label: Type
definition: VCR. Zoochory, Anemochory, Hydrochory, Barochory, Autochory.
notes: Type of dispersal, a controlled vocabulary is recommended.

label: Structure Dispersed
definition: VCR: Seed, Fruit, Vegetative structure, Spores, Gametes, Eggs, Offspring and Individuals.
notes: Structured that is dispersed for a given biologial propuse, a controlled vocabulary is recommended.

label: Distance
definition: Dispersal distance. e.g. 450 m.
notes: The distance reached by the structured dispersed.

label: Type
definition: Primary diet source. A controlled vocabulary is recommended.

label: Atomized Ecological Significance
definition: Ecological Significance element in structured format.

label: Unstructured Ecological Significance
definition: Ecological Significance element in text block format.

label: Atomized Environmental Envelope
definition: Environmental envelope of a species expressed as an enumeration of measures and parameters.

label: Unstructured Environmental Envelope
definition: environmentalEnvelopeas a a text block.

label: Atomized Feeding
definition: feeding elemento in structured format.

label: Unstructured Feeding
definition: feeding element in text block format.

label: Unstructured Distribution
definition: Distribution element in text block format.

label: Atomized Distribution
definition: Distribution element in structured format.

label: Distribution Scope
definition: List of regions structured and categorized.
notes:
A controlled vocabulary is recommended.
e.g. Historical, Current, Restricted and Wide.

label: Distribution Scope Type
definition: Categorization of scope qualifying the distribution presented in time (e.g. "prior 1900", "current", "projected", "winter"), in space (e.g. "in the Canary Islands", "Boreal"), by biological activity (e.g., "foraging distribution", "reproductive area"), or any other criteria . A controled vocabulary is recommended.

label: Temporal Coverage
definition: This field specifies temporal coverage of the distribution, and allows coverages to be a single point in time, multiple points in time, or a range of dates.

label: Geographic Entity
definition: Name of the geographic entity. A controlled vocabulary --as specified in the Catalogue element-- is recommended.
notes: e.g. Spain; Aguascalientas; Alabama; Ambon

label: Distribution Type
definition: Information about the distribution of the species based on the studied specimens collection sites data.

label: Geographic Entity
definition: Name of the geographic entity.
notes:
A controlled vocabulary --as specified in the Catalogue element-- is recommended.
e.g. Spain; Aguascalientas; Alabama; Ambon

label: Country
definition: The name of the country or major administrative unit in which the Location occurs.
notes: It is recommended to use a controlled vocabulary such as the Getty Thesaurus of Geographic Names.

label: State Province
definition: The name of the next smaller administrative region than country (state, province, canton, department, region, etc.) in which the Location occurs.

label: County
definition: The full, unabbreviated name of the next smaller administrative region than stateProvince (county, shire, department, etc.) in which the Location occurs.

label: Municipality
definition: The full, unabbreviated name of the next smaller administrative region than county (city, municipality, etc.) in which the Location occurs. Do not use this term for a nearby named place that does not contain the actual location.

label: Locality
definition: The specific description of the place. Less specific geographic information can be provided in other geographic terms (higherGeography, continent, country, stateProvince, county, municipality, waterBody, island, islandGroup). This term may contain information modified from the original to correct perceived errors or standardize the description.

label: Atomized Endemic
definition: List of areas structured and categorized by territories in which the endemic species appears (EndemicTo) in relation to a wider area (EndemicIn) given as geographical context.

label: Endemic To
definition: A territory in which an endemic species appear. A controlled vocabulary is recommended. The term may go from local to above-country levels.
notes: Examples: Giant panda (Ailuropoda melanoleuca (David, 1869) endemic to China. Quetzal Resplendent (Pharomachrus mocinno de la Llave, 1832) endemic to Mexico, Guatemala, Honduras, El Salvador, Nicaragua, Costa Rica and Panama.

label: Endemic In
definition: The area that works as a context for specifying endemic areas of a species. A controlled vocabulary is recommended. The term may go from local to above-country levels.
notes: If not specified, the Earth as a whole is assumed as the geographical context. Examples:  Vicu√±a (Vicugna vicugna Molina, 1782) endemic to the Andean region **in South America**. Manzanilla Real (Artemisia granatensis Boiss.) endemic in the peaks of Sierra Nevada (**in Spain**).

label: Unstructured Endemic
definition: Information on the endemicity of a species as a text block.

label: Atomized Habitat
definition: habitatAndDistribution element in structured format.

label: Unstructured Habitat And Distribution
definition: habitatAndDistribution element in text block format.

label: Endemic
definition: Ecological importance of the taxon. (Placeholder).

label: Habitats
definition: General description of the sites where the species is found (ecosystem, environment or microhabitat).

label: Distribution
definition: Species geographical distribution.

label: Unstructured Habitat
definition: habitat element in text block format.

label: Atomized Interaction
definition: interaction element in structured format.

label: Species Interaction
definition: Information category concerning relations between resources (instances or records, such as Occurrences, Taxa, Locations, Events,...).

label: Species Interaction Type
definition: String with the type of interaction. Each element is seperated by comma and each list of elements by.

label: Atomized Invasiveness
definition: invasiveness element in structured format.

label: Unstructured Invasiveness
definition: invasiveness element in text block format.

label: Origin
definition: Controlled vocabulary: Indigenous, Exotic, Unknown.

label: Presence
definition: Controlled vocabulary: Absent, SometimesPresent, Present, Unknown, Reported.

label: Persistence
definition: Controlled vocabulary: Persistent, Temporary, Transient, DiedOut, Unknown.

label: Distribution
definition: Controlled vocabulary: Widespread, Moderate, Localized, Unknown.

label: Harmful
definition: Controlled vocabulary: Yes, No, Potentially, Unknown.

label: Country Code
definition: The standard code for the country in which the Location occurs. Recommended best practice is to use ISO 3166-1-alpha-2 country codes.

label: State Province
definition:
The name of the next smaller administrative region than country (state, 
province, canton, department, region, etc.) in which the Location 
occurs.

label: County
definition:
The full, unabbreviated name of the next smaller administrative region 
than stateProvince (county, shire, department, etc.) in which the 
Location occurs.

label: Locality Name
definition: Protocol Specification on Locations.

label: Abundance
definition: Controlled vocabulary: Dominant, Common, Rare, Zero, Unknown, Monoculture.

label: Trend
definition: Controlled vocabulary: Stable, Declining, Unknown, Expanding.

label: Rate of Spread
definition: Controlled vocabulary: Rapid, Moderate, Slow, Unknown.

label: Regulatory Listing
definition: Controlled vocabulary: Prohibited, Restricted, NotConsidered, Unknown.

label: Locality Type
definition: Term borroewed from GISIN. An indication of the scope of the place referred under LocalityName.

label: What Impact
definition:
An indication of the actual impact as a free text string. e.g. destroys 
riparian vegetation, destroys irrigation systems, displaces Arvicola 
sapidus.

label: Vector
definition: By which means a species occupies a new territory. e.g. fishing boats; dirty boots, cars (Aedes albopictus).

label: Route
definition: This is equivalent and probably replaceable by gisin:route.

label: Impact Target
definition: This is equivalent and probably replaceable by gisin:impactTarget.

label: Impact Mechanism
definition: Mechanism of introduction or impact to a new location.

label: Atomized Life Cycle
definition: lifeCycle element in structured format.

label: Unstructured Life Cycle
definition: lifeCycle element in text block format.

label: Atomized Life Form
definition: lifeCycleForm element in structured format.

label: Unstructured Life Form
definition: lifeCycleForm element in text block format.

label: Ancillary Data
definition: The AncillaryData element contains information that could be an image, an audio, a list of references, a list of agents, rights, licenses...related with the element that belongs. It`s a redefinition of DataObject element from EOL scheme.

label: Metadata
definition: Management: actions aimed at conserving or recovering species / Conservation: undertaken interventions designed to preserve species.

label: Taxon Record
definition: Container for all elements pertaining a certain view or instance of a taxon, for instance, Festuca glauca Vill. as in Flora iberica, or Panthera onca as in https://enciclovida.mx/especies/34460-panthera-onca.

label: Dataset ID
definition: An identifier for the dataset.

label: dateStamp
definition: The date the metadata document was created or modified.

label: dataset
definition: The dataset element is a wrapper for all other elements relating to a single dataset as defined in eml.xsd (eml/dataset).
notes: https://eml.ecoinformatics.org/schema/

label: resourceLogoUrl
definition: The URI of an icon/logo symbolizing the project.

label: atomized migratory
definition: The regular, usually seasonal, movement of all or part of an animal population to and from a given area, which can occur in variable periods of time and even involve more than one generation broken down in specific elements.

label: unstructured migratory
definition: The regular, usually seasonal, movement of all or part of an animal population to and from a given area, which can occur in variable periods of time and even involve more than one generation as text block.

label: Causes
definition: Reasons for the species to move from one place to another in a specific lap.

label: Patterns
definition: Displacement of the species in space.

label: Routes
definition: Trajectory followed by the species.

label: Season
definition: Time of year in which a species migrates.

label: atomized molecular data
definition: MolecularData element in structured format.

label: unstructured molecular data
definition: MolecularData as a text block.

label: RelatedTo
definition: Specifies to which PlinianCore term the information contained under MolecularDataAtomized refers to. The controlled vocabulary is list of content-bearing PlinianCore elements.

label: Annual Cycle
definition: Set of changes or events that recurrently take place at the same time of year and are influenced by seasonal and interannual climate variations. Also called phenology, mainly in plants. In the case of migration, it only makes reference to the timing; other data about this are gathered in MigratoryClass.
notes: For example: reproduction, flowering, fruiting, emergence of insects, etc.

label: Behavior
definition: Responses, reactions or movements made by an organism in a particular situation.

label: Atomized Behavior
definition: Responses, reactions or movements made by an organism in a particular situation.

label: Unstructured Behavior
definition: Responses, reactions or movements made by an organism in a particular situation.

label: Dispersal
definition: The permanent spreading of individuals away from each other not including return. Dispersal determines the range over which genetic mixing occurs, and thus, the degree of homogeneity and inbreeding in a population.

label: Interactions
definition: Mutual or reciprocal actions or influences. Relations with products grown and stored by man (plagues) are also included.
notes: For example, predation, parasitism, mutualism, etc.

label: Life Cycle
definition: Life history of a living organism: The course of developmental changes in an organism from fertilized zygote to maturity or stages through which an organism passes.

label: Life Form
definition: General appearance. Characteristic mode of growth or occurrence associated to its environment, particularly for plants. Comprising its size, shape, texture and orientation.
notes: Example: tree, shrubs, herbs.

label: migratory
definition: The regular, usually seasonal, movement of all or part of an animal population of and from a given area, which can occur in variable periods of time and even involve more than one generation.

label: Miscellaneous Details
definition: Miscellaneus: notes attached to the taxon natural history information.

label: molecular data
definition: Information on the chemical structures and biological processes at the molecular level: DNA and proteins sequences, protein structures, expression profiles of genes protein domains, families of genes, mutations, polymorphisms, involvement in disease, ...
notes: Undeveloped. Placeholder for connecting with standards developed by specialists. For example, Standards for Data Exchange and Management from Scalalife (http://www.scalalife.eu/content/data)

label: Natural History Unstructured
definition: NaturalHistory element in text block format. This term is an unstructured alternative that may fit in an structured way in terms under the following categories:  TaxonomicDescription, LifeForm, LifeCycle, Reproduction, AnnualCycles, Feeding, Dispersal, Behavior, Interactions, MolecularData, Migratory, EcologicalSignificance, MiscDetails, EnvironmentalEnvelope.

label: Nomenclature and Classification Unstructured
definition: Information on the taxon's  name, synomyms, nomenclatural status, common names, and taxonomic hierarchy; plus  misc. details and ancillary data.

label: reproduction
definition: All data related to the production of offspring.

label: Ecological Significance
definition: Ecological importance of the taxon. (Placeholder).

label: Environmental Envelope
definition: Set of environmental conditions within which it is believed that the species can persist; that is, where its environmental requirements can be satisfied.

label: Feeding
definition: Information related to the food supply for the development and sustenance of the individual and/or its offspring.

label: Hierarchy
definition: Hierarchical categories. Modified from Linnean Core.
notes: Option: fill all or principal ranks and optionally provide keys.

label: Detail Unstructured
definition: MiscDetail element in text block format.

label: Atomized Detail
definition: MiscDetail element in structured format.

label: synonyms
definition: Different names for this taxon.

label: atomized population biology
definition: Population biology data in structured form.

label: unstructured population biology
definition: Population biology data as a text block.

label: Birth rate
definition: Ratio of births to the total number of individuals in a population in a time period.

label: Number individuals per observation
definition: Mean number of individuals per observation event or unit.

label: Average density
definition: Average of the densities obtained for a population.

label: Population trend
definition: Changes of a population over time and can include changes in  distribution, biogeography (e.g., size of population), life-history (e.g., birth and death rates), etc.

label: Recruitment
definition: Information on the process by which young individuals (e.g., seedlings, larvae, propagules) become part of the adult population. It can be rate, scale, a description, etc.

label: Population growth rate
definition: Growth rate of a population in a given time period, based on births, deaths, emigration and immigration.

label: Emigration
definition: Information on  individuals leaving a population.

label: Immigration
definition: Information on individuals entering a population.

label: Description life stages
definition: Sex/age categories or life stages of a species; can be size in the case of plants.

label: ProportionIndividuals per stage life
definition: Percentage of individuals that belong to each life stage in a population.

label: Carrying capacity
definition: Maximum population density possible as limited by the resources available for the population in the absence of predators and parasites.

label: AbundanceData
definition: The relative representation of a species population in relation to other species or multiple species in a particular territory.

label: DensityData
definition: Population size in relation to a defined space unit.

label: Pattern distribution
definition: The spatial arrangement of the individuals of a population in the territory it occupies.

label: Size
definition: Number of individual organisms in a population.

label: SexRatio
definition: Relative number of males to females in a population.

label: Fecundity
definition: In the context of a population, is the combined maximum potential of its individuals to produce offspring.

label: Mortality rate
definition: Probability of dying; the ratio between the number of deaths in a given time interval to the number of subjects alive at the start of this interval.

label: Unstructured Audiences
definition: List audience codes separated by means of comma or /.

label: Language
definition: The language of the taxon record, according to ISO 639.

label: Revision
definition: Creators, revision status and dates of the record.

label: atomized reproduction
definition: Reproduction element in structured format.

label: unstructured reproduction
definition: Reproduction element in text block format.

label: Unstructured Interaction
definition: interaction element in text block format.

label: atomized synonyms
definition: list of synonyms in a structured format.
notes: tsc:ScientificName

label: synonyms Atomized Type
definition: Type for atomized synonyms.
notes: Los "Type" los eliminamos ¬øno? (FP)

label: synonyms type
definition: A type of sequence of sequences of zero or more Atomized and Unstructured synonyms, each one with their optional ancillary data.
notes: Los "Type" los eliminamos ¬øno? (FP)

label: unstructured synonyms
definition: list of synonyms elements in a text block format.

label: Synonym name
definition: Scientific name of the synonym.
notes: tcs: ScientificName. An object that represents a single scientific biological name that either is, or appears to be, governed by one of the biological codes of nomenclature. These are not taxa. Taxa, whether accepted or not, are represented by TaxonConcept objects. Vernacular names are also dealt with under taxon concepts

label: Synonym status
definition: Nomenclatural Status
notes: dc:nomenclaturalStatus. http://rs.tdwg.org/dwc/terms/index.htm#nomenclaturalStatus

label: target audiences
definition: Type of sequence of sequences of zero or more Atomized and Unstructured synonyms, each one with their optional ancillary data.
usage: Biodiversity researchers, teachers and students, decision makers, professionals from another areas and general public.

label: Audience
definition: Repetitive concept where the target audiences are written one by one.
notes: Predetermined list: 01. Expert (High). 02. Knowledgeable (Medium). 03. General (Low).

label: Keys
definition: Dichotomic or multi-access key.

label: Keys
definition: Dichotomic or multientrance keys.

label: Atomized Full Description
definition: fullDescription element in structured format.

label: Unstructured Full Description
definition: fullDescription element in text block format.

label: Brief Description
definition: Brief description which reflect only the diagnostic characters, i.e. those that distinguish a taxon from other related or close taxa.

label: Full Description
definition: Complete and detailed account of the taxonomic and systematic characters, i.e. those that define and allow to recognize an organism.

label: unstructured taxonomic description
definition: TaxonomicDescription element in text block format.

label: Base Elements
definition: Basic information to identify the record.

label: Demography And Threat
definition: Information concerning the demographic aspects of the species, as well as the conservation status.

label: Habitat And Distribution
definition: Distribution of the species.

label: Identification Keys
definition: Tool for the identification of organisms, comprising a series of steps, each of which represents a question about one or more characters of the organism. Each step offers multiple alternatives, choosing one of them will lead us to the next step until ending, finally, in the name of the organism.
notes: Most printed keys have only two alternatives, so called dichotomous keys. A taxon includes a key or an identification of key in the subordinate taxons. If we are in a register of a genre, this register would include the keys of the species that this register includes, and if it√Ç¬¥s one specie, then it would include the key of the infraspecific rank (For plants: subspecies, variety forms)

label: Invasiveness
definition: Information about invasive exotic species that could threaten to ecosystem, habitats and species.

label: Natural History
definition: Relevant descriptive information about the species: Life Form, Life Cycle, Reproduction, Annual Cycles, Feeding, Dispersal, Behavior, Interactions, Molecular Data, Migratory, Ecological Significance, Miscellaneous Details, Environmental Envelope and Ancillary Data.

label: Record Metadata
definition: This element includes the information about the Version, Revision,the language and target audiences of the Taxon Record.

label: taxonomic description
definition: Description of Taxon.
notes: Description of Taxon: Brief description, Full description, Identification keys and Ancillary Data

label: unstructured territory
definition: Information associated mostly to vertebrates, referring to the territorial extension of the individual or group in terms of its activities (feeding, mating, etc.). As a text block.

label: Extent of occurrence
definition: Area contained within the shortest continuous imaginary boundary which can be drawn to encompass all the known, inferred or projected sites of present occurrence of a taxon, excluding cases of vagrancy.

label: Area of occupancy
definition: Area within its 'extent of occurrence' (see EOO) which is occupied by a taxon, excluding cases of vagrancy. The measure reflects the fact that a taxon will not usually occur throughout the area of its extent of occurrence, which may contain unsuitable or unoccupied habitats.

label: Direct Threats
definition: Direct threats are the proximate human activities or processes that have caused, are causing, or may cause the destruction, degradation, and/or impairment of biodiversity targets. Direct threats are synonymous with sources of stress and proximate pressures.
notes: Examples: unsustainable fishing or logging. Threats can be past (historical), ongoing, and/or likely to occur in the future.

label: Atomized Direct Threat
definition: directThreats element in structured format.

label: Unstructured Direct Threat
definition: directThreats element in text block format.

label: unstructured threat status
definition: Information about the status of the taxon.As a text block.

label: threat Status Atomized
definition: ThreatStatus element in structured format.

label: Threat category
definition: Description of the conservation status.

label: Authority
definition: Organism or institution that assess the status.

label: Applies to
definition: Location where the status is used.

label: Trophic Strategy
definition:
Tactic used to obtain energy or nutrients. A controlled vocabulary is 
recommended. e.g. Chemosynthetic organisms,Photosynthetic 
organisms,Parasites,Decomposers,Suspension feeders,Substrate feeders, 
Grazers,Fluid-feeders,Predators...

label: Trophic Strategy Remarks
definition: Information notes about specific feeding strategies.

label: Atomized Uses
definition: Ways in which species are utilized by people, including Folklore. Also applied to Animals and Fungi.

label: Unstructured Uses
definition: Uses in a unstructured format.

label: Source of Information
definition: Where does the observation come from? Reference citations should be given. Where appropriate, voucher specimen details should be provided (collector, number, date, herbarium) as well as details of the recorded informant (name, gender, approximate age, occupation, ethnic identity, locality and spoken language).

label: Use-Value
definition: What is the plant used for, or what negative values does it have.

label: Part Used
definition: Acc. TDWG Economic Botany. Which plant parts are used, or have any negative values.

label: Users
definition: Acc. TDWG Economic Botany. The user group who recognizes the value and/or use of the plant.

label: Organisms
definition: Acc. TDWG Economic Botany. Organisms which use the plant/plant parts.

label: Vernacular Name Use Annotations
definition: Acc. TDWG Economic Botany. The name of the taxon must be distinguished from the name of theplant parts, the names of any processing stages, and the final product name. Names used in trade should be identified. It should also be mentioned if any vernacular name refers to more than one taxon. The use of some names may be restricted to a time of year or occasion, or have sacred connotations. The language or dialect to which the names belong should be stated along with details of the ethnic group. Care should be taken with transliteration into the Roman alphabet; if a standard system exists, use it and note which one it is.

label: Production Details
definition: Definition:        Acc. TDWG Economic Botany. (where relevant). Give details of protection, cultivation, harvesting, yields, processing and storage methods used and take note of special tools, timing etc.

label: Means of Application-Administration
definition: Acc. TDWG Economic Botany. This is specific relevant for medicines, poisons .

label: Season of Availability-Use
definition: Acc. TDWG Economic Botany. The season in which the plant is available/is used and, if relevant, the time of day.

label: Conservation-Explotation Data
definition: Acc. TDWG Economic Botany. Frequency record of plants, details of regeneration, sustainability or over-exploitation and any locally imposed bans on felling or harvesting.

label: Use Type Atomized
definition: Acc. TDWG Economic Botany. Type of use: traditional, modern, industrial or just a possible use.

label: Economics
definition: Acc. TDWG Economic Botany. Real or potential existence of trade in live plants, plant parts or derivatives and, if so, the trade scale.

label: Rating Popularity
definition: Acc. TDWG Economic Botany. Assessment of the plant for its use and possible preference to other species, pointing out, in this case, which species are they.

label: Properties
definition: Acc. TDWG Economic Botany. Details of properties which influence its value for a specified purpose.

label: Potential
definition: Acc. TDWG Economic Botany. Potential increase in the use, cultivation or production or possibility of introduction in other areas or social groups.

label: Use Notes

definition: Specific purposes of the management actions. Each objective must be separated by ;

definition: Individual tasks in which a management project can be atomized. Each action must be separated by ;

definition: Each action must have one type. In the case that one action doesn't have type then put blank.

definition: Impact or value an species has either on the environment or on humans, and that justify management measures.

label: Scientific name
definition: Canonical name enforcing strict inclusion of only nomenclatural information - not taxonomic information. The name entered here must comply with rules and recommendations of the international nomenclatural code pertaining to the organisms (Zoological, Botanical, of Cultivated Pants, or Bacteriological).

label: Scientific Name
definition: Canonical name enforcing strict inclusion of only nomenclatural information - not taxonomic information.
